                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512 Flour/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-26T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1928—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>494. 1. Following from Shanghai: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 21, 12 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">noon.</hi>] Native press of June
                            16th published regulations promulgated by the Ministry of Finance to be
                            immediately effective calling for special tax of 5 cents per sack on
                            Chinese and imported flour. Washington agreement authorizes eventual
                            levying of surtax on dutiable imports but since flour is now duty free
                            Legation’s instruction is requested in reference to request of American
                            flour importers that some action be taken by the American
                            Government.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. It is suggested Legation be authorized to instruct Cunningham to protest as a
                    matter of record.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
